<section class="section section--alt" id="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Services FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Questions about the catalog.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a1">What accounting services does TechBrot deliver?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a1" data-open="false">
          <p>TechBrot delivers seven core service tracks: monthly bookkeeping (recurring fixed-fee close), cleanup bookkeeping (one-time structural fix), catch-up bookkeeping (historical work for months/years behind), QuickBooks services (setup, cleanup, migration, ongoing expertise), payroll management (multi-state with local jurisdiction tax), sales tax compliance (multi-state nexus and filings), and fractional CFO (strategic finance for growth-stage businesses). All engagements are fixed-fee with written scope before any work begins. Delivered by Certified Intuit ProAdvisors directly or through a curated network of vetted local accounting practices.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a2">How are engagements priced?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a2" data-open="false">
          <p>Every engagement is fixed-fee with written scope before any work begins. No hourly billing. Monthly bookkeeping runs $400-$2,500+/month based on transaction volume and complexity. QuickBooks cleanup runs $1,500-$15,000+ based on history depth. QuickBooks setup runs $750-$5,000+ based on entity complexity. Migration runs $2,500-$10,000+ based on platform and integration scope. Payroll management runs $150-$800+/month based on employee count and multi-state complexity. Sales tax compliance runs $250-$1,500+/month based on state count. Fractional CFO runs $3,000-$8,000+/month based on engagement depth &mdash; by application.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a3">Does TechBrot file tax returns?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a3" data-open="false">
          <p>No. TechBrot is an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; we deliver CPA-ready bookkeeping and operational accounting, but we do not file federal or state tax returns and we do not represent clients in front of the IRS. Tax filing and IRS representation are handled by your existing CPA or EA. If you do not have one, the operator network can refer you to a licensed professional in your state. The scope split is clean and stated up front in every engagement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a4">Which TechBrot service should I start with?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a4" data-open="false">
          <p>It depends on what shape your books are in. If your QuickBooks file has structural issues (unreconciled accounts, miscategorized transactions, misconfigured payroll), start with a cleanup engagement. If you&rsquo;re months or years behind on bookkeeping entirely, start with catch-up. If your books are clean but you need ongoing monthly close, start with monthly bookkeeping. If you&rsquo;re setting up QuickBooks for the first time or restructuring, start with setup. If you&rsquo;re migrating off QuickBooks Desktop or switching from another platform, start with migration. The 30-minute discovery call surfaces the right starting point &mdash; there is no wrong question and no obligation to engage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a5">Do all engagements include QuickBooks expertise?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a5" data-open="false">
          <p>Yes. Every TechBrot ProAdvisor holds active Intuit certifications across QuickBooks Online (Level 2), Desktop, Enterprise, and Payroll. QuickBooks expertise is the platform foundation across every service track &mdash; whether the engagement is monthly bookkeeping, payroll management, sales tax compliance, or fractional CFO. We work directly inside your QuickBooks file as accountant-users; we never operate in a parallel system.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a6">Are TechBrot services nationally available?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a6" data-open="false">
          <p>Yes. TechBrot delivers services to U.S. businesses in all 50 states. State-specific operational depth (Indiana CAGIT/COIT, Ohio RITA, Pennsylvania local PSD, multi-state payroll, multi-state sales tax nexus) is part of standard delivery. For engagements where in-state presence or specialized local knowledge matters, engagements route to a vetted local accounting practice through the operator network. See the find-an-accountant hub for state-by-state coverage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a7">What&rsquo;s the engagement process?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a7" data-open="false">
          <p>Every engagement begins with a 30-minute discovery call. Free, no obligation. We review your business, your current accounting situation, and recommend the right engagement structure &mdash; or honestly say &lsquo;not the right fit&rsquo; if that&rsquo;s the case. A written fixed-fee scope is delivered within three business days of the call. If you accept, the engagement begins. Onboarding for recurring engagements typically completes within two weeks; one-time project engagements have defined start and completion dates in the written scope. A named Certified ProAdvisor owns your account end-to-end.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a8">Is TechBrot affiliated with Intuit Inc.?</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-b1-silo-hub-faq-a8" data-open="false">
          <p>No. TechBrot Inc. is an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm. We hold active Intuit certifications and use QuickBooks software in our engagements, but TechBrot is not owned, employed, or operated by Intuit Inc. QuickBooks is a registered trademark of Intuit Inc. Our independence means recommendations follow your business needs, not vendor relationships.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

